frederick h waddell  federal reserve bank of chicago about us contact us museum careers frederick h waddell class a director term   chairman  chief executive officer northern trust corporationthe northern trust companychicago illinois biography frederick h waddell is chairman and chief executive officer of northern trust one of the worlds leading asset management asset servicing fund administration fiduciary and banking services firms serving successful individuals families and institutions worldwide the chicagobased yearold financial institution had  trillion in assets under custody and  billion in assets under management as of september     since joining northern trust in  waddell has held leadership positions in commercial banking strategic planning and personal financial services in march  he became head of the corporate  institutional services business unit and in february  was named president and chief operating officer of northern trust mr waddell was appointed chief executive officer on january   and named chairman in november    waddell is a member of the board of directors of the federal reserve bank of chicago the chicago council on global affairs the economic club of chicago the financial services roundtable the chicago club chicago urban league and the united way of metropolitan chicago he is a member of the commercial club of chicago and the civic committee of the chicago commonwealth club he is on the board of trustees of the art institute of chicago northwestern university the chicago symphony orchestra and northwestern memorial hospital he also serves on the trustees committee of the chicago community trust mr waddell serves as vice chairman of the corporate fund board of the john f kennedy center and is an executive advisor to the metropolitan planning council   waddell received a bachelor’s degree in government from dartmouth college and a master’s degree in business administration from the jl kellogg school of management of northwestern universit